Life cycle

componentDidMount : Called after render. called when all children are evaluted. If there are multiple component in one component, those will be mounted one by one in order. call setState in this.
componentWillMount: calling setState is prohibited here. Subscribe global events in this (example: window resize event)
componentDidUpdate: has previousStateProps and compare current props. 

Functional Component:  Need to declare it with const or let. It accepts only one parameter , that is 'Props'. Importing React is mandatory.

useEffect is called after render

React-Router->
       React-router-dom
       React-router-native

